ops-catchall.title: Creating Space Administrators Macro for Confluence

comments.body:
Note for when we do an upgrade:

After upgrade, update the second 1024 in setenv.sh file to 4096 (line76): 

cd /opt/atlassian/confluence/bin
opt/atlassian/confluence/bin$ sudo vi setenv.sh
```
# Set the Java heap size
CATALINA_OPTS="-Xms1024m -Xmx4096m ${CATALINA_OPTS}"
```
/opt/atlassian/confluence/bin$ sudo systemctl restart confluence

princeton_ansible.title: Mysql Users No Longer have permission to run sql-dump

comments.body:
Can bring to Ansible Open House. 

First noticed on Wednesday, February 8, so maybe patches on either Tuesday Jan. 31 or Feb. 7.

Depending on user running backups, this could potentially affect backups, but if they're running as root they probably wouldn't. 

This issue may argue for not auto-updating some utilities via apt. Had a similar issue with RabbitMQ. How might we balance stability with upgrades?
